'''Lethality''' is a term designating the ability of a [[weapon]] to kill.  Most often this term is used when referring to [[chemical weapons]], [[biological weapons]], or their chemical components.  The use of this term denotes the ability of these weapons to kill, but also the possibility that they may not kill.  Reasons for the lethality of a weapon to be inconsistent, or expressed by percentage, can be as varied as minimized exposure to the weapon, previous exposure to the weapon minimizing susceptability, degradation of the weapon over time and/or distance, and incorrect deployment of a multi-component weapon.

This term can also refer to the after-effects of weapon use, such as [[Nuclear_fallout|Nuclear Fallout]], which has highest lethality nearest the deployment site, and in proportion to the subject's size and nature; e.g. a child or small animal.

